<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI - 9JAN97 - FIGHTING BREAKS OUT IN TURSUN ZADE</title>
<h1>OMRI - 9JAN97 - FIGHTING BREAKS OUT IN TURSUN ZADE</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 10 Jan 97 10:12:57 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#82">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#82">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#82">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#82">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0083.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 9JAN97 - FIRST BRIGADE TO LEAVE TURSUN ZADE"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0081.html">ctroy@mail.sorosny.org: "OMRI - 8JAN97 - TROUBLE IN TAJIKISTAN'S "WILD WEST""</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     FIGHTING BREAKS OUT IN TURSUN ZADE. Despite a presidential order to <br>
     withdraw his forces from the Tursun Zade area, elements of Col. Mahmud <br>
     Khudaberdiyev's First Brigade attacked outlaw forces in the city on 8 <br>
     January, international media reported. Khudaberdiyev had moved his <br>
     force close to the city claiming that Tursun Zade's criminal band, <br>
     loyal to former Popular Front commander Kadyr Abdullayev, raided the <br>
     First Brigade's headquarters on 29 December to steal weapons, in the <br>
     process killing one officer. Khudaberdiyev said the attack was sparked <br>
     by the government's refusal to do anything about the situation. He is <br>
     demanding Abdullayev return the weapons and vacate the city. Efforts <br>
     by the Tajik government, Russian forces in Tajikistan, and the UN <br>
     observer mission to mediate the isolated conflict have not met with <br>
     any success. Both government and opposition representatives say the <br>
     fighting in Tursun Zade will not have an impact on peace talks being <br>
     held in Tehran. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0083.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 9JAN97 - FIRST BRIGADE TO LEAVE TURSUN ZADE"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0081.html">ctroy@mail.sorosny.org: "OMRI - 8JAN97 - TROUBLE IN TAJIKISTAN'S "WILD WEST""</a>
