<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI - 30DEC96 - NEW TAJIK AGREEMENT FOR PEACE</title>
<h1>OMRI - 30DEC96 - NEW TAJIK AGREEMENT FOR PEACE</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 06 Jan 97 14:38:04 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#76">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#76">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#76">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#76">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0077.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 3JAN97 - TERRORISM IN TAJIK CAPITAL"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0075.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 2JAN97 - TAJIK-IRANIAN RELATIONS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     NEW TAJIK AGREEMENT FOR PEACE. Tajik President Imomali Rakhmonov and <br>
     United Tajik Opposition leader Said Abdullo Nuri signed an agreement <br>
     in Moscow on 23 December, international media reported. The agreement <br>
     provides for a general amnesty, an exchange of all prisoners, and a <br>
     promise by both sides to create the necessary conditions for the <br>
     return of Tajik refugees. Most importantly, the agreement establishes <br>
     a reconciliation council to be headed by an opposition representative. <br>
     The council will spend 12-18 months reviewing proposed amendments to <br>
     the Tajik Constitution. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0077.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 3JAN97 - TERRORISM IN TAJIK CAPITAL"</a>
