<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: Interfax 29Dec96 Rakhmonov Issues Privatization Decree</title>
<h1>Interfax 29Dec96 Rakhmonov Issues Privatization Decree</h1>
<i>fsu@mail.sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 30 Dec 96 16:46:31 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#74">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#74">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#74">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#74">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0075.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 2JAN97 - TAJIK-IRANIAN RELATIONS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0073.html">fsu@mail.sorosny.org: "Interfax 26Dec96 Tajik Group Frees Joint Commission Member"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     TAJIK PRESIDENT ISSUES DECREE TO SPEED UP PRIVATIZATION<br>
     <br>
     DUSHANBE, Dec 29 (Interfax) - President Emomali Rakhmonov<br>
     of  Tajikistan   Sunday  signed   a   decree   to   accelerate <br>
     privatization.<br>
        The decree  aims to  form the securities market, speed up<br>
     privatization, change  the social structure of the population, and <br>
     attract foreign and national investments, Tajik government experts <br>
     told Interfax.<br>
        The decree  assesses the  transformation  of  enterprises<br>
     into joint-stock  companies as  the preliminary  stage of  the <br>
     privatization of large and medium-sized businesses. The decree defines <br>
     privatized  enterprises as  enterprises in  which  the controlling <br>
     interest is not state-owned.<br>
        In  line   with  the   decree,  the   transformation   of<br>
     enterprises  into   public  joint-stock  companies  should  be <br>
     completed before September 1, 1997.<br>
     To prevent  the appearance of monopolies on some markets,<br>
     the existing structure of enterprises will have to be revised, the <br>
     Tajik  president said. Enterprises on some markets will be privatized <br>
     only  after they  are broken  down into a number of units.<br>
     The president  instructed the  government to  prepare and<br>
     approve a  procedure to  break down enterprises for the future <br>
     privatization of their units.<br>
        The president  also ordered  that a  state commission for<br>
     economic reform,  which will  include the  prime minister, the <br>
     presidential economics  adviser, the  economics,  finance  and justice <br>
     ministers, and the National Bank governor, be created.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
