<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     TAJIK FIGHTING CONTINUES, MOVES CLOSER TO CAPITAL. An attempt by Tajik <br>
     government forces to retake the city of Garm has been repelled by <br>
     opposition forces who captured the city last week, Russian sources <br>
     report. Opposition forces used artillery and tanks to drive back <br>
     government troops. Attacks have also been reported as close as 13 <br>
     kilometers from the capital Dushanbe. A Russian helicopter came under <br>
     gun and grenade fire at Dushanbe airport on 4 December. -- Bruce <br>
     Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
