<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: Interfax-11 Nov--INTER-TAJIK SETTLEMENT DISCUSSED IN MOSCOW</title>
<h1>Interfax-11 Nov--INTER-TAJIK SETTLEMENT DISCUSSED IN MOSCOW</h1>
<i>fsu@mail.sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Tue, 12 Nov 96 14:10:34 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#48">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#48">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#48">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#48">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0049.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "INTERFAX-12 NOV 96--CONTINUED CONFLICT WILL SPLIT TAJIKISTAN"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0047.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 11Nov96 - Tajik Opposition Releases Prisoners"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 INTER-TAJIK SETTLEMENT DISCUSSED IN MOSCOW<br>
 <br>
 MOSCOW, Nov 11 (Interfax) - Leader of the Ismaelites, Aga<br>
 Khan VI, last Sunday met in Moscow with leader of the Movement for the  <br>
 National Revival  of Tajikistan, ex-prime minister of Tajikistan Abdumalik <br>
 Abdulldzhanov.<br>
 Abdulldzhanov told  Interfax Monday  that the  talks  had<br>
 lasted for  an hour  and dealt  with a  wide range  of  issues pertaining to <br>
 the situation in Tajikistan and Afghanistan. "We came to  the conclusion  that <br>
 the  Talibs' advancement  to the northern  provinces  of  Afghanistan  may  <br>
 have  an  extremely negative impact on the situation in Tajikistan," he said.<br>
 He quoted  Aga Khan  as saying  that Russia  is playing a<br>
 special role in the settlement of the inter-Tajik conflict. He also said  that <br>
 Aga  Khan  favored  "an  increasing  role  and influence of  international <br>
 organizations,  above all the U.N. and the OSCE, in settling the Tajik crisis."<br>
 Neighboring Uzbekistan  is expected  to play a great role<br>
 in the Tajik settlement, said Abdulldzhanov.<br>
 He  said  that  the  leaders  of  the  Tajik  opposition,<br>
 including armed  opposition,  are  ready  to  sit  down  at  a negotiating <br>
 table  with the  Tajik official  authorities,  "if certain cardinal  terms, <br>
 which have been rejected by President Emomali Rakhmonov,  are fulfilled."  What <br>
 is meant here is the formation of  an interim government comprising <br>
 representatives of the opposition, political parties and public organizations, <br>
 he said.<br>
 <br>
 (c) Interfax, 1996<br>
 <br>
 <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
