<!-- body="start" -->
     TAJIK OPPOSITION RELEASES PRISONERS. Tajik opposition forces have <br>
     freed the last of 37 police hostages they captured on 24 October near <br>
     Komsomolabad, AFP reported on 8 November. The release of the remaining <br>
     hostages comes after the government freed four members of the <br>
     opposition held in government jails. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
     [As of 12:00 CET]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
