<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     <br>
     TAJIK OPPOSITION RELEASES 10 HOSTAGES. Ten of 35 police officers taken <br>
     prisoner by the Tajik opposition near Komsomolabad on 27 October were <br>
     released unconditionally on 1 November, according to ITAR-TASS and <br>
     RFE/RL. Opposition leader Said Abdullo Nuri said the remaining <br>
     hostages would be freed when the government removed its checkpoints <br>
     along roads in central Tajikistan, the opposition's original demand, <br>
     but added a new demand that four opposition members be freed from <br>
     government jails. -- Bruce Pannier and Abbas Djavadi<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
