<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI--30 Oct 1996--TAJIK OPPOSITION MAKES NEW DEMANDS</title>
<h1>OMRI--30 Oct 1996--TAJIK OPPOSITION MAKES NEW DEMANDS</h1>
<i>arichter@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Wed, 30 Oct 96 12:23:21 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#41">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#41">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#41">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#41">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0042.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "OMRI--1 Nov 1996-CENTRAL ASIANS AT DONOR CONFERENCE IN JAPAN"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0040.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "OMRI--30 Oct --FOUR CENTRAL ASIAN STATES ATTEND TEHRAN CONF."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 <br>
 TAJIK OPPOSITION MAKES NEW DEMANDS. The United Tajik Opposition (UTO) insists <br>
 that the National Reconciliation Council that the UTO has proposed be comprised <br>
 40% by the Movement for the Islamic Revival of Tajikistan, 40% by other <br>
 opposition groups, and just 20% by government representatives, ITAR-TASS <br>
 reported on 28 October. The next round of talks between the Tajik government <br>
 and UTO, to be held in Moscow, are not expected anytime soon, a spokesman for <br>
 the UTO said. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0042.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "OMRI--1 Nov 1996-CENTRAL ASIANS AT DONOR CONFERENCE IN JAPAN"</a>
