<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI-8 OCT 1996--TALIBAN EXTENDING OLIVE BRANCH?</title>
<h1>OMRI-8 OCT 1996--TALIBAN EXTENDING OLIVE BRANCH?</h1>
<i>kkhalmatov@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Wed, 09 Oct 96 11:04:59 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#35">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#35">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#35">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#35">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0036.html">kkhalmatov@sorosny.org: "OMRI--15 OCT 1996--TAJIK OPPOSITION ATTACK"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0034.html">kkhalmatov@sorosny.org: "OMRI--4 OCT 1996--ALMATY PREPARES FOR CIS SUMMIT"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     TALIBAN EXTENDING OLIVE BRANCH? A spokesman for the Taliban movement <br>
     claims that Central Asia has nothing to fear from the group that now <br>
     controls most of Afghanistan, Rusian Public TV (ORT) reported on 7 <br>
     October. The acting foreign minister of the Taliban, Muhammed Ghous, <br>
     called upon the UN "to convince Uzbekistan, Tajikistan, Kazakstan, and <br>
     Kyrgyzstan not to meddle in Afghanistan's internal affairs and the <br>
     Taliban for their part will not interfere in the affairs of other <br>
     countries." A radio broadcast originating in Pakistan on 6 October <br>
     announced that the Taliban would soon send representatives to the <br>
     Central Asian states as a demonstration of the group's "brotherly <br>
     love" for the region, Radio Rossii reported on 6 October. However, <br>
     Ghous reportedly said "we do not want Russia to forget the lesson they <br>
     were taught here," referring to the Soviet military campaign in <br>
     Afghanistan in the 1980s. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0036.html">kkhalmatov@sorosny.org: "OMRI--15 OCT 1996--TAJIK OPPOSITION ATTACK"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0034.html">kkhalmatov@sorosny.org: "OMRI--4 OCT 1996--ALMATY PREPARES FOR CIS SUMMIT"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
