<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI--18 September 96--CEASEFIRE IN KARATEGIN VALLEY</title>
<h1>OMRI--18 September 96--CEASEFIRE IN KARATEGIN VALLEY</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Wed, 18 Sep 96 12:40:16 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#25">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#25">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#25">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#25">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0026.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI-- 20 September 96--STABILITY RETURNS TO EASTERN TAJIKIS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0024.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--17 September 1996--RAHKMONOV IN CHINA"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     CEASEFIRE IN KARATEGIN VALLEY. Tajik government officials and <br>
     opposition field commanders agreed to a ceasefire in the Karategin <br>
     valley on 16 September, Western and Russian news agencies reported. <br>
     The agreement appears to stipulate that checkpoints established by <br>
     both sides are to be lifted in Garm, Jirgatal and Tajikabad, thereby <br>
     permitting transit on the solitary artery linking the country's <br>
     capital with the Pamirs and Kyrgyzstan. -- Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
