<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI--30 August 1996--Border Guard Officers Confer</title>
<h1>OMRI--30 August 1996--Border Guard Officers Confer</h1>
<i>eurasia@mail.sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 30 Aug 96 10:04:47 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#18">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#18">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#18">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#18">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0019.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--9 September 96--TAJIK OPPOSITION SEIZES DJIR-GATAL"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0017.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--29 August 96--RUSSIA, TAJIKISTAN GIVEN OBSERVER STATUS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     BORDER GUARD OFFICERS CONFER. Senior border guard officers from <br>
     Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan, Uzbekistan, and Russia agreed in <br>
     Moscow on 29 August to take "additional measures" to defend the Tajik- <br>
     Afghan border, ITAR-TASS reported the same day. Russia appears to be <br>
     strengthening the hand of its border troops in Tajikistan in order to <br>
     face down some 1,000 armed Tajik rebels who are reportedly ready to <br>
     enter Tajikistan from Afghanistan. The presidents of Kyrgyzstan and <br>
     Kazakstan have both voiced their concern over the increase in tension <br>
     along the border and have called on the Tajik government and <br>
     opposition to resolve the conflict. -- Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0019.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--9 September 96--TAJIK OPPOSITION SEIZES DJIR-GATAL"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0017.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--29 August 96--RUSSIA, TAJIKISTAN GIVEN OBSERVER STATUS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
