<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI--29 August 96--WHO CONTROLS WHAT IN TAJIKISTAN</title>
<h1>OMRI--29 August 96--WHO CONTROLS WHAT IN TAJIKISTAN</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Thu, 29 Aug 96 13:10:18 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#16">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#16">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#16">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#16">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0017.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--29 August 96--RUSSIA, TAJIKISTAN GIVEN OBSERVER STATUS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0015.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--28 August 96--KILLERS OF TAJIK JOURNALIST RECEIVE DEAT"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     WHO CONTROLS WHAT IN TAJIKISTAN? Military sources in Dushanbe claim <br>
     government troops in central Tajikistan have consolidated and expanded <br>
     their positions, freeing a stretch of road northwest of the town of <br>
     Tavil-Dara, ITAR-TASS reported on 28 August. Government forces retook <br>
     Tavil-Dara on 23 August but sources in Dushanbe say the town is <br>
     deserted after three months of fighting in the area. The opposition's <br>
     Radio Voice of Free Tajikistan reported on 28 August that opposition <br>
     fighters hold the northern road from Faizabad, 70 kilometers east of <br>
     Dushanbe, to Jirgatal, 80 kilometers from the Kyrgyz border. The <br>
     report admitted that opposition fighters held the road only <br>
     "partially" during the daytime but "completely at night." The report <br>
     also claimed government forces could only reach the Tavil-Dara area <br>
     via a southern route through Kulyab and the Karnak Pass. -- Bruce <br>
     Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0017.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--29 August 96--RUSSIA, TAJIKISTAN GIVEN OBSERVER STATUS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0015.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--28 August 96--KILLERS OF TAJIK JOURNALIST RECEIVE DEAT"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
