<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Tajikistan: OMRI--20 August 96--KYRGYZSTAN SEEKS TAJIK COOPERATION</title>
<h1>OMRI--20 August 96--KYRGYZSTAN SEEKS TAJIK COOPERATION</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Tue, 20 Aug 96 14:45:02 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#6">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#6">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#6">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#6">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0007.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--21 August 96--FBI IN TRANSCAUCASUS AND CENTRAL ASIA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0005.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--20 August 96--TAVIL-DARA IN OPPOSITION HANDS"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     KYRGYZSTAN SEEKS TAJIK COOPERATION IN REFUGEE PROBLEM. The Kyrgyz <br>
     government has asked Tajik authorities to speed up the repatriation of <br>
     Tajik refugees in Kyrgyzstan, ITAR-TASS reported on 19 August. Kyrgyz <br>
     Minister of Labor and Social Security Zafar Khakimov stated there are <br>
     15,000 Tajik refugees registered in Kyrgyzstan, mainly in the Osh and <br>
     Jalalabad areas. Khakimov said the concentration of Tajik refugees in <br>
     Kyrgyzstan's southern regions was creating tensions, specifically in <br>
     the Betken district, an area already possessing a Tajik majority and <br>
     still claimed by Dushanbe as belonging to Tajikistan. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
