<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     TAVIL-DARA IN OPPOSITION HANDS. Opposition forces occupied the central <br>
     Tajikistan town of Tavil-Dara on 17 August, Reuters reported. This was <br>
     admitted by a Tajik government representative to the group, Zafar <br>
     Ikromov, who is monitoring the ceasefire agreement. The Tajik Defense <br>
     Ministry claims its forces withdrew in order to prevent losses among <br>
     the civilian population of the town. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
     <br>
