<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Uzbekistan: OMRI - 6JAN97 - STRENGTH OVER JUSTICE IN UZBEKISTAN</title>
<h1>OMRI - 6JAN97 - STRENGTH OVER JUSTICE IN UZBEKISTAN</h1>
<i>eurasia@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 06 Jan 97 14:58:05 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#69">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#69">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#69">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#69">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0070.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 8JAN97 - LAW ON POLITICAL PARTIES IN UZBEKISTAN"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0068.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 30DEC96 - KYRGYZ PRESIDENT IN UZBEKISTAN"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     STRENGTH OVER JUSTICE IN UZBEKISTAN. A coat of arms for Uzbekistan's <br>
     capital, Tashkent, was issued on 4 January, ITAR-TASS reported the <br>
     same day. The emblem's components are an open gate topped by an <br>
     oriental dome on a background of a mountain and rivers framed by <br>
     flowers, a grape vine and a plane tree in blossom. Encircling all of <br>
     this are the words "In Strength is Justice" [Kuch Adolatadir], a <br>
     mis-translation of the words "Rasti Rusti" [In Justice is Strength] <br>
     from Firdausi's Persian epic The Book of Kings [Shah Namah]. Since the <br>
     late October celebration of the birth of Tamerlane, the improperly <br>
     rendered text has increasingly been associated with him and is to be <br>
     found on numerous billboards, the wall of a museum erected to lionize <br>
     the great conqueror-builder, as well as the star of Samarkand state <br>
     medal in Uzbekistan. -- Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0070.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 8JAN97 - LAW ON POLITICAL PARTIES IN UZBEKISTAN"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0068.html">eurasia@sorosny.org: "OMRI - 30DEC96 - KYRGYZ PRESIDENT IN UZBEKISTAN"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
