<!-- body="start" -->
     UZBEK HISTORIOGRAPHY. Academics working under President Islam <br>
     Karimov's Academy for State and Societal Construction plan to issue a <br>
     three-volume "Modern History of Uzbekistan," Khalq Sozi reported on 27 <br>
     November as monitored by the BBC. The book will cover Tsarist <br>
     colonialism, "Soviet Colonialism," and Uzbekistan's modern history of <br>
     independence. The academics, led by historian Hamdam Sodiqov, are <br>
     battling against "false conceptions about the history of independence" <br>
     and "former Kremlin and Communist Party sycophants," the report said. <br>
     -- Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
