<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 <br>
 JAPANESE GIVE MONEY TO UPGRADE UZBEK AIRPORTS. The Japanese government <br>
 announced on 30 October that a credit of 15.5 billion yen (more than $140 <br>
 million) will be given to Uzbekistan to upgrade airports in Samarkand, Bukhara <br>
 and Urgench, ITAR-TASS reported. The three cities date back to the days of the <br>
 Silk Route and are the sites of many historical monuments. The Uzbek government <br>
 hopes that improvement in the airports will aid the tourism industry, with <br>
 profits then channeled into industry. -- Bruce Pannier<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
