<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0044.html">arichter@sorosny.org: "OMRI--30 Oct --FOUR CENTRAL ASIAN STATES ATTEND TEHRAN CONF."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 NEW POLITICAL OFFICE CREATED IN UZBEKISTAN. In an address to the cabinet, Uzbek <br>
 President Islam Karimov announced that Qobiljon Obidov will be appointed to the <br>
 newly-created position of first deputy prime minister with special <br>
 responsibility for agriculture and water resources, Uzbek TV reported on 29 <br>
 October. Given recent poor harvests in the Syrdarya and Jizzak regions (see <br>
 OMRI Daily Digest, 29 October 1996), Karimov has called for greater oversight <br>
 and a more defined division of labor in the presidential apparatus. -- Roger <br>
 Kangas<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
