<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 <br>
 <br>
 POLITICAL HEADS ROLL IN UZBEKISTAN. Uzbek President Islam Karimov dismissed the <br>
 Hokim (Governor) of Syrdarya region on 28 October, Uzbek TV reported. <br>
 Ghulomqodir Khasanov was officially relieved of his duties because of his <br>
 failure to meet grain and cotton harvest targets. He will be replaced by Deputy <br>
 Prime Minister Utkam Ismailov. Karimov dismissed the Hokim of Jizzak region, <br>
 Alisher Toshkenboev, on 25 October for the same reason. The firings follow a <br>
 pattern of Hokim replacements that began after last fall's poor grain harvest. <br>
 -- Roger Kangas<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
