<!-- body="start" -->
 <br>
 PAKISTAN'S PRESIDENT VISITS UZBEKISTAN. Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari on 20 October <br>
 concluded a three-day visit to Uzbekistan, where he met President Islam Karimov <br>
 and other government officials, ITAR-TASS reported. The two leaders signed <br>
 several agreements, ranging from anti- drug trafficking cooperation to <br>
 joint-venture trading. According to Uzbek TV on 18 October, bilateral trade is <br>
 restricted because of the blockage of transport routes across Afghanistan. <br>
 Trade between Uzbekistan and Pakistan stood at $12.7 million for the first six <br>
 months of 1996, up from $11.6 million for all of 1995. -- Roger Kangas<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
