<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     UZBEK MEDIA SHOOTS BACK. Uzbek media has lashed out at what it deems <br>
     to be the Russian media's recent slanderous coverage of Uzbekistan, <br>
     RFE/RL reported on 10 October. The usually cautious Uzbek media was <br>
     responding to a number of articles that appeared in late September in <br>
     Izvestiya, Nezavisimaya gazeta, and Komsomolskaya pravda pointing to <br>
     corruption and political repression in Uzbekistan. The Russian press <br>
     was also charged with wrongly accusing Tashkent of allying itself with <br>
     Afghan General Abdul Rashid Dostum, an ethnic Uzbek, to seize <br>
     territory from Tajikistan. The Uzbek media said the "hostile coverage" <br>
     was aimed at Russia's efforts to play "big brother" in the region. -- <br>
     Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
