<!-- body="start" -->
     MAYLI-SUU CLEANUP PLANNED. Kyrgyz and Uzbek environmental agencies <br>
     have agreed to cooperate to reduce the danger at more than 20 <br>
     radioactive waste sites near the Kyrgyz town of Mayli-Suu, according <br>
     to a report in Aziya- Ekonomika i zhizn [No. 40] monitored by the BBC. <br>
     Successive heavy rains and mudslides have meant that the dump sites <br>
     may be contaminating the Mayli-Suu River and through it various canals <br>
     that irrigate the Ferghana Valley. -- Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
