<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Uzbekistan: OMRI--10 September 1996--HUMAN RIGHTS CONFERENCE IN TASHKENT</title>
<h1>OMRI--10 September 1996--HUMAN RIGHTS CONFERENCE IN TASHKENT</h1>
<i>eurasia@mail.sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 13 Sep 96 18:23:21 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#18">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#18">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#18">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#18">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0019.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--13 September 1996--COUNCIL OF CIS BORDER FORCES MEETS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0017.html">eurasia@mail.sorosny.org: "OMRI--13 September 1996--OLD TECHNIQUES TO INJECT NEW IDEAS."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     HUMAN RIGHTS CONFERENCE IN TASHKENT. A three-day OSCE-sponsored <br>
     conference on human rights--bringing together non-governmental <br>
     organizations operating in Central Asia, government officials, and <br>
     government-selected media representatives--opened in Tashkent on 11 <br>
     September, Western agencies reported. Human rights are far from <br>
     respected in Central Asia with print and broadcast media carefully <br>
     censored or directly controlled by the government and minimal <br>
     tolerance shown for political opposition. Among a litany of other <br>
     human rights violations, AFP noted that 40 journalists have been <br>
     killed in Tajikistan since 1992, some 30 prisoners of conscience are <br>
     presently in Uzbek jails, and 600 prisoners died in Kazakstani jails <br>
     of tuberculosis last year and another 101 were executed. The venue of <br>
     the conference is considered a further signal of Uzbekistan's desire <br>
     to soften the regime's image abroad. -- Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0019.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--13 September 1996--COUNCIL OF CIS BORDER FORCES MEETS"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0017.html">eurasia@mail.sorosny.org: "OMRI--13 September 1996--OLD TECHNIQUES TO INJECT NEW IDEAS."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
