<!-- body="start" -->
     <br>
     <br>
     KARIMOV ON HUMAN RIGHTS, OPPOSITION. Speaking to parliament on 29 <br>
     August, Uzbek President Islam Karimov said his government is committed <br>
     to boosting cooperation with international human rights organizations, <br>
     Reuters reported the same day. In the speech that marked the country's <br>
     fifth year of independence, Karimov praised the republic's political <br>
     stability and added that there is a need for political "alternatives" <br>
     as long as they are "constructive." -- Lowell Bezanis<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
