<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     UZBEKISTAN'S CENTRAL BANK CUTS REFINANCING RATE. The Central Bank of <br>
     Uzbekistan has announced that in late August and September the <br>
     refinancing rate at which it provides short-term credits to other <br>
     financial institutions will be set at 4% per month, down from 5% in <br>
     July-August and 7% in the first half of the year, Delovoi mir reported <br>
     on 27 August. Lower refinancing rates reflect the government's success <br>
     in keeping inflation low. The average monthly inflation rate in the <br>
     first half of 1996 was 4%, compared to 8% during the same period a <br>
     year earlier. -- Natalia Gurushina<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
