<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Uzbekistan: OMRI ECON. DIGEST--15 August 96--SALARIES CUT AS PUNISHMENT</title>
<h1>OMRI ECON. DIGEST--15 August 96--SALARIES CUT AS PUNISHMENT</h1>
<i>tlankina@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Fri, 16 Aug 96 13:46:23 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#5">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#5">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#5">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#5">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0006.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--21 August 96--FBI IN TRANSCAUCASUS AND CENTRAL ASIA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0004.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI ECON. DIGEST--15 August 96--TAX COLLECTION WOES"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     SALARIES CUT AS PUNISHMENT IN UZBEKISTAN. Uzbek President Islam <br>
     Karimov issued a decree to tie regional administrators' salaries to <br>
     their ability to abide by a June decree to lower cash emissions, <br>
     ITAR-TASS reported on 13 August. Administrators who do not fully carry <br>
     out the decree can be fined 20% of their salary, while those that do <br>
     so will receive bonuses equivalent to 30% of their salary. To date, <br>
     only Tashkent administrator Kazym Tulyaganov and two of his deputies <br>
     have received bonuses, while all other administrators who have dealt <br>
     with this issue have been fined. -- Roger Kangas<br>
     <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0006.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI--21 August 96--FBI IN TRANSCAUCASUS AND CENTRAL ASIA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0004.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "OMRI ECON. DIGEST--15 August 96--TAX COLLECTION WOES"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
