<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     TAX COLLECTION WOES IN UZBEKISTAN. In an effort to curtail tax evasion <br>
     by Uzbek enterprises, President Islam Karimov issued a decree to allow <br>
     the State Tax Committee to confiscate property held by companies with <br>
     fiscal arrears, according to a 13 August Halq sozi report monitored by <br>
     the USIS. In addition, all banks are now required to submit reports on <br>
     the commercial activities of enterprises under investigation. -- Roger <br>
     Kangas<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
