<title>OMRI and Other Excerpts for Uzbekistan: OMRI - Uzbek President Proposes Arms... - Aug 5, 1996</title>
<h1>OMRI - Uzbek President Proposes Arms... - Aug 5, 1996</h1>
<i>agalietti@sorosny.org</i><br>
<i>Mon, 12 Aug 96 14:55:14 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="index.html#0">[ date ]</a><a href="thread.html#0">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#0">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#0">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0001.html">tlankina@sorosny.org: "Central Asia Monitor, Issue No. 3"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
     UZBEK PRESIDENT PROPOSES ARMS EMBARGO ON AFGHANISTAN. <br>
     Uzbek President Islam Karimov has sent an official petition to <br>
     the UN Security Council calling for a general arms embargo on <br>
     Afghanistan, ITAR-TASS reported on 3 August. Pakistan supports <br>
     the proposal, and top Pakistani officials are currently in <br>
     contact with their Uzbek counterparts to work out the details. <br>
     Karimov first suggested such an embargo at the UN in October 1995. <br>
     -- Roger Kangas<br>
     <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
