REFERRAL	 - I am interested in psychiatry as a responsible aspect of an "open society" --- a psychiatry that appreciates the reality of mental illness on the one hand but avoids a facile slide into reductionisms and ideologies on the other -- be they psychopharmacological, psychotherapeutic, or behavioral.  Such reductionisms lead to abuses of psychiatry:  labelling political dissidents, members of new religious movements, and others who are "different" as mentally ill; regarding all mental suffering or even mental inefficiency as mental illnesses, medicating and otherwise "treating" all human problems 
