<PRE>I wish such a thorough website such as yours, dedicated to an open society, could lead others to possible employment opportunities in Eastern/Central Europe and Russia.  We all do not have the capacity to engage in major funding projects.  However, many young students like myself would like to partake in, anyway possible, in reform measures in the countries in question.  Every website talks about the tremmendous business opportunities, a "new frontier". I agree, but unless a company/organization has gobs of money to take the risk to invest in these countries, nothing really can be done, or seems so.  What if Soros set up a program for students, grads, etc. to work at the grassroots level of programs in exchange for room and board and the experience?  This would be a profitable experience for both.</PRE>
